The Council consists of the following 25 members:
The Special Secretary of the Office for Children, Youth, and Families or the Special Secretary's designee;
The State Superintendent of Schools or the State Superintendent's designee;
The Secretary of Health and Mental Hygiene or the Secretary's designee;
The Secretary of Juvenile Services or the Secretary's designee;
The Secretary of Human Resources or the Secretary's designee;
The Secretary of Budget and Management or the Secretary's designee;
One member of the Senate of Maryland appointed by the President of the Senate;
One member of the House of Delegates of Maryland appointed by the Speaker of the House;
The following members appointed by the Governor:
One individual with experience or expertise with the Maryland Medical Assistance Program;
One local health officer;
One local superintendent of schools;
Three individuals from local jurisdictions, including at least one representative of a local management board;
Three individuals who represent community leaders from organizations and faith communities that have experience or expertise with the services offered in school-based health centers;
Three consumers of school-based health care including students and their parents;
A pediatrician;
A nurse practitioner who serves children in a school-based health center;
A member of the Maryland Assembly of School-Based Health Centers;
A dental health professional; and
A representative of the Mental Hygiene Administration or a core service agency.
